claim.claim-text:
A semiconductor device (200, 800), comprising:
a semiconductor substrate (210, 810) having a first conductivity type and a top substrate surface (212, 812);
a buried layer (220, 820) below the top substrate surface, wherein the buried layer has a second conductivity type that is different from the first conductivity type;
a sinker region (222, 822) between the top substrate surface and the buried layer, wherein the sinker region has the second conductivity type, and an isolation structure is formed by the sinker region and the buried layer;
an active device in the semiconductor substrate within a portion (230, 830) of the substrate contained by the isolation structure, wherein the active device includes a current carrying region (236, 238, 836, 838) selected from a source region and a drain region; and
a resistor circuit (160) connected between the isolation structure and the current carrying region.

A method for forming a semiconductor device (200, 800), the method comprising the steps of:
forming (1404) a buried layer (220, 820) below a top substrate surface (212, 812) of a semiconductor substrate (210, 810) having a first conductivity type, wherein the buried layer has a second conductivity type that is different from the first conductivity type;
forming (1404) a sinker region (222, 822) between the top substrate surface and the buried layer, wherein the sinker region has the second conductivity type, and an isolation structure is formed by the sinker region and the buried layer;
forming (1406) an active device in a portion (230, 830) of the semiconductor substrate contained by the isolation structure, wherein the active device includes a current carrying region (236, 238, 836, 838); and
forming (1408) a resistor circuit (160) connected between the isolation structure and the current carrying region.
